main event: A report of unidentified flying objects in Casper, Wyoming on January 26, 1967.
interesting points: The object was observed to be bright at first but then changed characteristics and disappeared into darkness., The report suggests that the object was likely an aircraft, although the physical evidence was deemed insufficient., There were multiple vehicles noted in the report, including a disc-like vehicle moving rapidly across the sky., The object hovered silently and seemed to produce a mist or fog-like effect., The object was estimated to be as large as a house but no specific details could be identified.
witness description: Encountered the object while observing from a distance, estimated size but unable to see details.
